body.p: For recurring fair value measurements categorised within Level 3 of the fair value hierarchy, the IFRS requires a reconciliation from the opening balances to the closing balances for each class of assets and liabilities. An entity might disclose the following for assets to comply with paragraph 93(e) and (f) of the IFRS:

entry.none: Fair value measurements using significant unobservable inputs (Level 3)

entry.p: Total gains or losses for the period
Change in unrealised gains or losses for the period included in profit or loss for assets held at the end of the reporting period
(Note: A similar table would be presented for liabilities unless another format is deemed more appropriate by the entity.)
